# Discussion

This report combines **classifier validation** on a held-out test set with **morphometry**
on the full cohort after selective rejection. On the test split, baseline accuracy is
**{{baseline_accuracy_pct}}**; selective rejection improves accepted-only accuracy to
**{{selective_accuracy_pct}}** while deferring **{{n_rejected}}** ambiguous cells
(**{{coverage_pct}}** coverage). That trade-off is appropriate when morphometry should
describe only cells the model judged with confidence.

On the full dataset, **{{good_fraction_pct}}%** of scored detections were accepted as good
(median per-frog yield **{{yield_median_pct}}%**). Morphometric summaries therefore describe
the **accepted subset**, not every segmented object. Frogs with low yield may be
under-represented.

Cell size varies substantially between frogs (ICC **{{icc_area}}**; per-frog mean area
**{{frog_mean_area_min}}--{{frog_mean_area_max}} $\mu$m$^2$**). Nucleus--cell scaling is
{{scaling_interpretation}}: larger cells tend to have proportionally smaller nuclei (lower N/C).
The mixed slope (**{{regression_mixed_slope}}**) is smaller than the pooled OLS slope
(**{{regression_ols_slope}}**), reflecting that much nucleus--cell correlation is
**between frogs**, not only within them.

# Glossary

| Term | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| **Good cell** | A segmented cell accepted by the quality classifier for morphometry. |
| **Bad cell** | A segmentation rejected as poor quality. |
| **Selective rejection** | Three-way policy: accept as good, accept as bad, or defer as uncertain. |
| **Coverage** | Fraction of test cells that received a good/bad decision (not deferred). |
| **Accuracy** | Fraction of all labelled cells classified correctly. |
| **Recall** | Of truly good cells, fraction the model kept. |
| **Precision** | Of cells called good, fraction that are truly good. |
| **Specificity** | Of truly bad cells, fraction the model discarded. |
| **F1** | Harmonic mean of precision and recall. |
| **N/C ratio** | Nucleus area divided by cell area (unitless). |
| **Yield / good fraction** | Share of scored detections accepted as good. |
| **ICC** | Share of cell-area variation explained by which frog a cell came from. |
| **Allometry** | How nucleus size scales with cell size; slope = 1 is isometric, < 1 is negative allometry. |
| **Temperature scaling** | Post-hoc calibration of classifier probabilities. |
